<LP>
   PUBLISHING: Western Publishing Group Inc. agreed to buy
Sight &amp; Sound Inc., a producer of children's interactive
electronic storybooks, as well as toys and games that talk.
Terms weren't given.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   ACQUISITION: New York-based Insight Communications Co.
U.K. closed the acquisition of a 50%, controlling interest in
Clyde Cablevision, a 4,800-subscriber cable-TV system serving
Glasgow, Scotland, for #2 million ($3.4 million).
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: Carolco Pictures Inc., Los Angeles, named Rene
Bonnell, chairman of Canal Plus Productions, a director,
increasing the board to 13. . . . Walt Disney Co. said
Harrison Ellenshaw was named to the new post of vice
president, visual effects, for Walt Disney Pictures, a
subsidiary of Walt Disney Studios, a unit of the parent. He
recently served as visual effects supervisor on Touchstone
Pictures' "Dick Tracy."
